It's more common to castle here, but I decided to put some more pressure against the e4-pawn.
An interesting alternative variation would be 10. Bxe6!? fxe6 11. Nxe6 Qd7 12. Nxg7  Kf8 and white would surely have an advantage. Therefore I think 9...0-0 would have been better.
Notice how 10... b4 11. Nd5 exd5 12. exd5 Bc8 13. Bxf6 gxf6 is good for white with good initiative.
? Black has a cramped position, but this move allows him to get back in the game. 11. Bxe6 fxe6 12. Nxe6 would have been better I think.
I now feel that 11... Nc5 would have been a stronger option here. After for example 12.a3 black is slightly better.
12. Nd5!? exd5 13. Bxd5 Nxd5 14. exd5 looks interesting but I think black can hold here.
?? Grabbing the pawn almost instantly, but 12... O-O secures black's position.
White is winning here. The e6-pawn is very weak, especially because the black king is still in the centre and the black queen isn't very well placed on e7.
